slipped out, while Linton was engaged in
timidly rebuffing the advances of 'a friendly
sheep-dog. But he was too much on the
alert to be cheated--as I closed the door, I
heard a cry, and a frantic repetition of the
words--

"Don't leave me! I'll not stay here! I'll
not stay here!"

Then the latch was raised and fell--they
did not suffer him to come forth. I mounted
Minny, and urged her to a trot; and so my
brief guardianship ended.
